title: ICE on with rustc 1.26.0-nightly (f5631d9ac 2018-03-24) and later

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I got ICE for sometime and also searched in issues but cannot find a relative one.
Sorry for not able to produce the minimal cases to pin down the actual failing case in my code base by simply reverting my code. x

This issue does not exists in `nightly-2018-03-21`. Error message  as follows:
